## 14. Frontend Dataflow (Typical Example)

### Trigger Payment Flow

```
User clicks "Trigger Payout"
 → Frontend validates selection
 → POST /payments/trigger
 → Backend executes & logs
 → Response returned
 → Frontend refreshes pending list
 → Ledger auto-updated
```

No frontend state mutation without backend confirmation.

---

## 15. Non-Negotiable API Rules

1. No frontend-calculated money
2. No silent success
3. No partial writes without response
4. Ledger is append-only
5. All financial APIs are POST
6. Idempotency required for payments

